<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="choose-v">choose <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /tʃuːz/    美 /tʃuːz/  </p>
<p>(chose, chosen)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>选择；挑选：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He had to <strong>choose between</strong> death and dishonour.
他必须在丢掉性命和忍受屈辱之间作出选择。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>choose sb to do sth / choose sth for sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I chose her a present. / I chose a present for her.
我为她挑选了一份礼物。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>choose sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We choose John to represent our club.
我们选约翰来代表我们俱乐部。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>choose sb as / for / to be:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We chose her as / for / to be president.
我们选她当总裁。</p></div>

<h3 id="select-choose-pick">辨析 select, choose, pick</h3>
<p>三者都有“选择”之意。<br />
<strong>select ** 指“精选”，是从同类的许多事物或人中仔细辨别后选出最合适的。
</strong>choose ** 泛指选择，可不带宾语。
**pick ** 表示随意挑选，通常所指的事项不很重大，是不太正式的用词。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She picked a piece of cake for herself. 
她为自己挑了一块蛋糕。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>宁愿；决定</strong></h4>
<p>to prefer or decide to do sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You can drop in on me if you choose.
如果你愿意可以顺便来我家坐坐。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>choose + (wh-) to do:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She let him choose which restaurant to eat at.
她让他来选在哪家餐厅吃饭。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I became interested in biology and chose to learn it when I entered the college. 
我开始对生物感兴趣，并在上大学的时候选择学生物。</p><footer>2012 重庆</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="cannot-choose-but-do">cannot choose but (do)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不得不；只好：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He cannot choose but attend the party.
他只好去参加这次聚会。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>To my delight, I <strong><em>_</em></strong> (choose) from hundreds of applicants to attend the opening ceremony.   （2015 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. was chosen  </p></div>